    <section class="guide-takeaways">
      <h2>Key Takeaways</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>SDE multiples are the standard for Main Street businesses - they match how SBA lenders underwrite acquisitions</li>
        <li>EBITDA multiples apply to larger, professionally managed businesses ($5M+ revenue)</li>
        <li>Asset-based valuation applies when assets exceed the earnings-based valuation (distressed or asset-heavy businesses)</li>
        <li>DCF is rarely appropriate for small businesses due to projection uncertainty and irrelevance to SBA financing</li>
        <li>The correct method is the one that matches your buyer type - SBA buyers underwrite on SDE, PE buyers underwrite on EBITDA</li>
      </ul>
